DAY 9 - MULTIPLE ATTRIBUTES

A constructor can receive multiple values.

Example:

class Person:

    def __init__(self, name, gender):
        self.name = name
        self.gender = gender

    def show_details(self):
        print(self.name)
        print(self.gender)

person1 = Person("Ishu", "Female")

Output:

Ishu
Female

Important:

Class = Person

Object = person1

Parameters = name, gender

Attributes = self.name, self.gender

Values = Ishu, Female

Method = show_details()

Constructor = __init__()



